User Manual Group 8 Calendar

In order to add an event the user simply double clicks the day he or she wants to add the event. The user can use the arrows to scroll through the months. The current day is highlighted in blue. Then a menu will pop up which will have two options add event or calendar. The user should click add event and then specify the start and end time along with the event name and event type. In order to add event the user should scroll up and click the plus sign in the upper left corner. That will take the user back to the calendar and add item menu and then the user clicks calendar to go back to main calendar view. The user can click the day again to make sure the event is there. In order to see the events in weekly view, the user can simply click the weekly view option on the bottom. 
